title: Did Russia Use Dart Frog Poison To Kill Opposition Leader Alexei Navalny? | 10 News+
description: Russia has long been accused of using exotic poison to eliminate its opponents.   But now there's claims the Kremlin weaponised a toxin found in the skin of a dart frog, to murder outspoken dissident Alexei Navalny.   The poison, which is called Epibatidine, is said to be 100 times more lethal than morphine.

description: A new, exclusive poll for 10 News+ has revealed a staggering 62 per cent of Americans believe the justice department engaged in a cover up involving the Epstein files.   Only 27 per cent of Americans think the Trump administration has handled the release of the files well, just 20 per cent of Republicans. title: Former US President Barack Obama Says Aliens Are Real | 10 News
description: Former US President Barack Obama has jokingly confirmed that aliens are real in an interview with podcaster and YouTuber Brian Tyler Cohen before shutting down the conspiracy around a Nevada Air Force base.  The 44th president said, “They’re real, but I haven’t seen them."  “They’re not being kept at Area 51. There’s no underground facility, unless there’s this enormous conspiracy, and they hid it from the president of the United States,” Obama said. title: India Celebrates After Win Over Pakistan In T20 World Cup | 10 News
description: Celebrations have erupted across India after the team’s T20 World Cup victory over Pakistan on Sunday.  Fans poured onto the streets for high-energy festivities in Mumbai and Sri Lanka, cheering the win with drums, chanting, fireworks and proudly waving the nation’s flag to mark a historic win for the Indian cricket team.  India defeated Pakistan by 61 runs at R. Premadasa Stadium, Colombo, Sri Lanka. title: Alleged Bondi Terror Attack Gunman Naveed Akram Fronts Sydney Court On 59 Charges | 10 News
description: The man accused of carrying out the Bondi Beach terror attack has fronted court for the first time, appearing via video link from a maximum-security prison.   Naveed Akram is facing 59 charges, and today, said just two words during the brief hearing.   Johnpaul Gonzo was there and filed this report.
